
***    USAGE    ***
How to use program:

1. Run command 'make' to create executable.
2. Run command './run' to count locality characteristics. By default input data are taken from file input/data.txt, but this can be changed in this script. 
3. View results in characteristics.csv.
3a. Some more results can be viewed in bin/output.log. This also can be changed in 'run' script.

P.S. If necessary, run 'make clean' to delete all results (in bin/ dir) or run 'make clean_all' to also delete executable.

